---
// NOTE: This is a general-purpose template covering cookies and data/GDPR
// rights. Have it reviewed by an attorney and keep it accurate as you add
// tools (e.g. analytics or advertising pixels).
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
import { SITE, ADDRESS_LINE } from '../lib/site';
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Cookie Policy & Privacy (GDPR) | Carpet Mart"
  description="How Carpet Mart uses cookies and handles your personal data, including your rights under the GDPR and similar privacy laws."
  heading="Cookie Policy & Privacy"
  pageName="Cookie Policy"
  path="/cookie-policy"
  lastUpdated="June 16, 2026"
>
  <p>
    This policy explains how {SITE.legalName} ("Carpet Mart," "we," "us" or "our") uses cookies and
    handles personal information on <a href={SITE.url}>{SITE.url}</a> (the "Site"), and the rights you
    have under the EU/UK General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and similar laws.
  </p>

  <h2>Information we collect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Information you provide.</strong> When you submit our quote/contact form, we collect the
      details you enter — typically your name, email, phone number, town, the products you're
      interested in, and your message.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Information collected automatically.</strong> Like most websites, our hosting provider
      may log basic technical data such as your IP address, browser type and the pages you visit, for
      security and to keep the Site running.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Cookies &amp; similar technologies</h2>
  <p>Cookies are small files stored on your device. We aim to keep our use of them minimal:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Essential cookies.</strong> Used only where necessary for the Site to function — for
      example, a secure session cookie for staff signing in to our private admin area.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Third-party embeds.</strong> Pages that display a map use an embedded mapping service
      (Google Maps), which may set its own cookies. That data is handled under the provider's own
      privacy policy.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We do not currently use advertising or cross-site tracking cookies. If we add analytics or
    marketing tools in the future, we will update this policy.
  </p>

  <h2>How we use your information</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>To respond to your quote requests and questions and to provide our products and services.</li>
    <li>To schedule measures, deliveries and installations.</li>
    <li>To operate, secure and improve the Site.</li>
    <li>To comply with our legal obligations.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Legal bases for processing (GDPR)</h2>
  <p>Where the GDPR applies, we rely on the following legal bases:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Consent</strong> — when you submit a form to ask us to contact you.</li>
    <li><strong>Legitimate interests</strong> — to run our business, respond to inquiries and keep the Site secure.</li>
    <li><strong>Contract</strong> — to take steps at your request before, and in connection with, a purchase or installation.</li>
    <li><strong>Legal obligation</strong> — where we must retain certain records.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How your information is shared</h2>
  <p>
    We do not sell your personal information. We share it only with trusted service providers who help
    us operate (for example, website hosting and the database that stores form submissions), and when
    required by law. These providers process data on our behalf under appropriate safeguards.
  </p>

  <h2>Data retention</h2>
  <p>
    We keep quote requests and related correspondence only as long as needed to respond to you, fulfil
    your project, and meet legal or record-keeping requirements, after which we delete or anonymize it.
  </p>

  <h2>Your privacy rights</h2>
  <p>
    Depending on where you live, you may have the right to access, correct, delete or receive a copy of
    your personal information; to object to or restrict certain processing; and to withdraw consent. To
    exercise any of these rights, contact us using the details below and we will respond as required by
    applicable law. You also have the right to lodge a complaint with your local data-protection
    authority.
  </p>

  <h2>Managing cookies</h2>
  <p>
    You can control or delete cookies through your browser settings, and set your browser to warn you
    before accepting them. Blocking essential cookies may affect how parts of the Site work.
  </p>

  <h2>Children's privacy</h2>
  <p>The Site is intended for adults and is not directed to children, and we do not knowingly collect data from children.</p>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this policy from time to time. The "Last updated" date above reflects the most recent
    revision.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact us</h2>
  <p>
    To ask about this policy or exercise your privacy rights, contact Carpet Mart at
    <a href={`tel:${SITE.phoneHref}`}>{SITE.phone}</a>, <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a>,
    or {ADDRESS_LINE}.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
